   <title type="text">Nubian Monasteries</title>
   <content type="html"><![CDATA[<a href="http://www.nubianmonasteries.pl/">Nubian Monasteries</a><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><img alt="http://www.nubianmonasteries.pl/upload/201404/web2r.jpg" class="shrinkToFit decoded" height="52" src="http://www.nubianmonasteries.pl/upload/201404/web2r.jpg" width="200" /> </blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><div style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: inherit;"><span style="font-size: x-small;">This page aims at making information on Byzantine Nubia&nbsp;and Nubian monasteries in particular&nbsp;available  to wider audience. It will present projects regarding Nubian  monasticism but also Nubian culture in general from the times between  Napata and Funj kingdoms. </span></span></div><span style="font-family: inherit;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"></span></span><div style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: inherit;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><br />Two  years ago I've started a program aimed at synthesis on Nubian  monasteries. Thanks to the hospitality of the Oriental Institute,  University of Chicago and generosity of the Foundation for Polish  Science and de Brzezie Lanckoronski Foundation I lead a project carried  out by a team of early career European scholars publishing the Qasr  el-Wizz monastery. The monastery has been fully excavated by George  Scanlon on behalf of the Oriental institute in 1965, yet only two  preliminary reports in Journal of Egyptian Archaeology has been  published. Our aim is to publish the entire material recovered at the  site and made this exceptional collection available for the public... </span></span></div></blockquote><blockquote class="tr_bq"><div class="module module-Menu"><div class="module-content tm-menu tm-menu-7"><ul class="menu"><li class="root"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://www.nubianmonasteries.pl/">Home</a></span></li><li class="root"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://chicago.academia.edu/ArturObluski">Author</a></span></li><li class="root"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://nubianmonks.nazwa.pl/">Nubia in the Byzantine Period</a></span></li><li class="root"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://nubianmonks.nazwa.pl/general-information.html">Ghazali</a></span></li><li class="root"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="mailto:aobluski@nubianmonasteries.pl">Email</a></span></li></ul></div></div></blockquote>]]></content>
